scenarioDescription:
The TOI-763 Exoplanetary System


Overview

TOI-763 is a star with 0.92 times the mass of the Sun, and 0.9 times its radius. It is located 310.26 light years away from the solar system.

TOI-763 is known to have 2 exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the TOI-763 system


TOI-763 b

TOI-763 b was discovered by the Transiting Exoplanet Survey Satellite (TESS) observatory, in 2020-08, using the transit method. Its semi-major axis is 0.06 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of TOI-763 b is 9.794 times the mass of Earth. The radius of TOI-763 b is 2.280 that of Earth. At more than 10 Earth masses, TOI-763 b is an ice giant, a planet that is made up mostly of volatiles like water, amonia and methane, and enveloped by a dense hydrogen and helium atmosphere, much like Uranus and Neptune in our solar system.


TOI-763 c

TOI-763 c was discovered by the Transiting Exoplanet Survey Satellite (TESS) observatory, in 2020-08, using the transit method. Its semi-major axis is 0.10 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of TOI-763 c is 9.324 times the mass of Earth. The radius of TOI-763 c is 2.630 that of Earth. At more than 10 Earth masses, TOI-763 c is an ice giant, a planet that is made up mostly of volatiles like water, amonia and methane, and enveloped by a dense hydrogen and helium atmosphere, much like Uranus and Neptune in our solar system.
